1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper deals with the secrecy capacity of a wiretap channel, which is a fundamental concept in information theory. 
2. cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) - The paper focuses on secure communication and deals with the problem of transmitting confidential messages in the presence of an eavesdropper. 
3. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper deals with a cooperative wiretap channel, which is a type of network communication. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper considers the use of an Amplify and Forward (AF) relay, which is a control system used in communication networks. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper deals with the transmission of messages, which can be considered a type of multimedia communication.
